	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "10th / 16th century (d. 952 / 1545)Egyptian poet, mystic and Šāfiʻī scholar. Author of al-Ḥizb.\n\nThe additional names given above are based on al-Ziriklī.\n\nal-Ziriklī notes that Brockelmann mixes his biography with that of his father Abū al-Ḥasan al-Bakrī. The mix-up is repeated in Encyclopaedia of Islam, where the entry on al-Bakrī is written by Brockelmann.\n               " .
